/*!
\page array_fliplr FLIPLR Reverse the Columns of a Matrix

<p>
Section: \ref sec_array "Array Generation and Manipulations"
\section USAGE
Reverses the columns of a matrix.  The syntax for its use is
\verbatim
   y = fliplr(x)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> is matrix.  If <tt>x</tt> is an N-dimensional array then
the second dimension is reversed.
\section Example
The following example shows <tt>fliplr</tt> applied to a 2D matrix.

\if FRAGMENT
